      • getNewServiceConnection

        @NonNull
protected android.content.ServiceConnection getNewServiceConnection()
        Here we create the ServiceConnection with the navigation service. We use the route and simulate settings used in TGBaseTurnByTurnFragment.Options. This can be used as an example of how to handle the callbacks from TGNavigationService.NavigationCallback. Note that you do not need to supply a TGMap for this to work, but if you would like to get updates on the map then you must call TGNavigationService.setTgMap(TGMap)
        Specified by:
        getNewServiceConnection in class TGBaseTurnByTurnFragment
